observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Management:
a) Direct the General Services Officer with the Inventory Committee to conduct complete physical & count and classify properly the accounts presented in the RPCPPE;
b) Require the Municipal Accountant to prepare the necessary adjusting entries in order to reconcile the balances per financial statements against the RPCPPE prepared by the General Services Office and make full disclosures of the related information in the Notes to the Financial Statements;
c) Direct the concerned department to complete the one-time cleansing of PPE accounts intended to establish PPE balances that are verifiable as to existence;
d) Compute or trace any discrepancy with the RPCPPE and prepare proper adjusting entries to correct the same;
e) Conduct proper procedures to dispose of the unserviceable properties, in coordination with the accounting department to derecognize the same in the books of the agency;
f) Complete the disposal procedures of the remaining unserviceable properties in coordination with the accounting department to derecognize the same in the books of the agency;
g) The Municipal Accounting Office refer to the General Services Office records in reporting the properties. Also, the Management adhere to the procedures in the derecognition of non-existing/missing PPEs without available record of accountability as prescribed in COA Circular No. 2020-006 to establish PPE balances that are verifiable as to existence, condition and accountability.

We recommended and the Management agreed to direct the ensuing department heads the enumerated courses of actions:
To the Municipal Accountant:
i. Compute or trace any discrepancy with the RPCPPE and prepare proper adjusting entries to correct the same;
To the Municipal General Service Officer:
i. Conduct complete physical count of all LGU properties together with other members of the Inventory Committee of the LGU and report the same using the prescribed RPCPPE form in NGAS Manual for LGUs;
ii. Maintain proper and complete records of the PPEs, particularly the stock cards and property cards in compliance with the applicable rules and regulations;
iii. Conduct proper procedures to dispose of the unserviceable properties, in coordination with the accounting department to derecognize the same in the books of the agency; and
Direct the Local Chief Executive (LCE) to direct the concerned personnel to implement the “one-time cleansing” of PPE account, following the guidelines and procedures provided in COA Circular No. 2020-006, to establish the reliable PPE balances that are verifiable as to existence, condition and accountability.

We recommended the following:
The Inventory Committee headed by the General Services Officer shall maintain updated and properly accomplished property cards for property accountabilities;

The Inventory Committee headed by the General Services Officer shall conduct a complete actual physical count of PPE. The result of the physical count shall be reported in RPCPPE in accordance with the above guidelines and are promptly reconciled with accountabilities recorded in the books of accounts and the property cards and submit the same to the Office of the Auditor.

We recommended the following:
 The Municipal General Services Officer shall maintain updated and properly accomplished property cards for property accountabilities;
 The Inventory Committee headed by the General Services Officer shall conduct a complete actual physical count of PPE. The result of the physical count shall be reported in RPCPPE in accordance with the above guidelines and are promptly reconciled with accountabilities recorded in the books of accounts and the property cards and submit the same to the Office of the Auditor.
